Program to prorate a specific number of hours among all projects.

example: python prorate.py -t 8
         PROJECT_2   : 3.2
         PROJECT_1   : 4.8

% python prorate.py --help
usage: PRORATE [-h] [--version] [--time TIME] [--verbose] [--describe]

*note*: Program makes use of termcolor (http://pypi.python.org/pypi/termcolor)
'sudo pip install termcolor'

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --version             show program's version number and exit
  --time TIME, -t TIME  the amount of time to prorate
  --verbose, -v         Show a detailed description of the formula being done
  --describe, -d        Show the project data we are using
